Detail shots of my mural and artworks for @jamesonsniagara in @fallsviewcasino 
.
.
About the project
The murals represent the transformative power of the Falls. It showcases the progression of water forming into plants and birds, personifying this fluid element as the sculptor in nature that influences all. The dynamic project consists of three large-scale murals, five printed glass pieces and seven individual artworks totalling an area of over 1,200 square feet.
.
.

Self Portrait 📸 
.
Spring is my favourite season of the year. Seeing the transformation and regrowth of nature is an inspiring cycle with many symbolisms and metaphors that I apply in my body of work. As an Artist, nature is the best creator and teacher of all things. For me, emphasizing the vibrancy and beauty of our natural surroundings serves as a way to connect with ourselves and the land that we live in. I also believe that this encourages an appreciation and care toward our environment.
.
Check out some of my art pieces and murals that celebrate the spirit of nature➡️
.

My artwork entitled “Tahanan” is the newest piece to be acquired by @cibc for their art collection and art exhibition called CIBC Ambition Takes Flight. I’m grateful that international travellers coming to Canada will be able to see this artwork. The inspiration was my homeland the Philippines🇵🇭 with the intention of encouraging individuals to explore tropical destinations.

“Tahanan” Tagalog word for home.
Diptych.
60 x 40 in.

You can view this piece at Terminal 1 International Baggage Hall, Carousel 8 at @torontopearson Airport ✈️ along with other Canadian Artists and their work.

Mahalo Maui🌺

It was a great time to experience the beauty and culture of Hawaii these past few days. I used this as an opportunity to be present, calm and a moment to appreciate the natural wonders of nature. What better way to invigorate and inspire the mind while being in paradise?

Respect and care for the land are so prevalent in Pacific Islander culture. There’s an aura surrounding us and nature provides us with the energy to feel its presence, beauty, and power. It's both surreal and captivating.

Finding moments of stillness is so important as an Artist. Whether that's through meditation or nature, it helps to ground you and have a better sense of clarity. Trips like these definitely fuel and inspire the creative spirit.

Here are a couple of photos I took in paradise 📸

Jason Zante is a Filipino- Canadian artist based in Toronto, Canada. He received his B.DES in Graphic Design from OCAD University in 2020. With a multidisciplinary background, he specializes primarily in digital art, illustration, and mural installation. 

He creates surreal and stylized compositions of dream-like environments dominated by colours and floating symbols that recall imagination and familiarity. Influenced by nature and surreal painters, Jason’s work radiates with vibrant colours that form a sensorial experience and escapism. His work depicts themes of natural landscapes and everyday leisure. At times, he also draws references from his Filipino culture to incorporate into his artworks.

Zante has worked on many notable site-specific commissions including a mural for The Four Seasons Hotel Toronto (2021), a 1200 sf permanent art and mural for Fallsview Casino Resorts in Niagara Falls (2022), and art billboards for Cadillac Fairview Toronto Eaton Centre (2021). His work is in private collections of TD Bank, Cboe Global Markets, and CIBC. His clients also include BentallGreenOak, Klick Health, Wattpad, The Globe & Mail, NBA Canada and Deciem.

Zante’s creations have been featured by Forbes, Architectural Digest, Complex magazine, CTV News, Blogto, The Toronto Star, Yorkville Murals, Highsnobiety, Hypebeast and Artnet.

Thank you to everyone who attended the opening night of my solo exhibition at the @stacktmarket hosted by @iccontemporary. We’ve gotten over 1000 visitors in the gallery so far and look forward to seeing and meeting you.

A preview behind the process of creating “The Blue Collection” a series that invites stillness and tranquility amidst a busy world filled with complex details. A visual escape to embrace solitude and a space for self-reflection to find clarity and vitality in the simplicity of the landscape.
 
Available next week for everyone in my “Collectors List”.
Sign up for my newsletter to get the info. Link in my Bio.
 
Going back to my roots as a painter and translating my ideas and concepts into acrylic paintings is a fulfilling but creative challenge I’ve decided to pursue this summer. Working digitally to create the composition and using tools like an airbrush and tape for my desired effect has been so much fun to explore. This is just the beginning and I’m excited to take you along the journey!

Mural commissioned by @deciem The Abnormal Beauty Company for their factory location in Etobicoke, Ontario. 

12ft height x 40ft length.
Digital painting printed on Vinyl.

About the Mural:
The factory is re-imagined as a magical place. The elements within the mural are composed of various structural shapes inspired by the factory machines and production process. It's a symphony of stylized forms and playful symbols that mimic the assembly line from the creation lab to the final product. The community of individuals behind the creation of the product is highlighted in each tableau inside the arches. Central to this composition is the final product that radiates all the energy like a shining star. 

Thank you to @jasonsantos01 , Carlos and the install team for working alongside this project 💖
